body: This didn't build when rebased against incoming. @dbp said he would look at it.

This should be working (it just had some versions that had to be updated to 0.5). Looking at the diff, I'm not sure how that merge commit got in there - I just spent a long time fighting with rebase to get this to mostly work, but somehow that ended up in there. Hopefully it's not a problem.
No worries, I'll rebase this and that should make the merge commit go away.

I'm also getting an error:

```
compile_and_link: x86_64-apple-darwin/stage1/lib/rustc/x86_64-apple-darwin/bin/rustdoc
warning: no debug symbols in executable (-arch x86_64)

cp: x86_64-apple-darwin/stage1/lib/rustc/x86_64-apple-darwin/lib/ is a directory (not copied).
make: *** [x86_64-apple-darwin/stage2/lib/] Error 1
```

This is on Mac OS X (Lion) if it matters.

I tried building this after running `make clean`. I got as far as running the pretty-printing tests (so, pretty far) but then got:

```
compile_and_link: x86_64-apple-darwin/test/rustdoctest.stage2-x86_64-apple-darwin
error: unknown input file type: x86_64-apple-darwin/stage2/bin/rustc
```

Any ideas?

Hmm. my make check isn't running all the tests, it seems :) I figured out a target that will reproduce this: 
make check-stage2-T-x86_64-apple-darwin-H-x86_64-apple-darwin-rustdoc-dummy

And the problem was that I didn't update those targets (as I didn't know they existed). I should be able to figure out what is going on (now that I can actually reproduce). I will update once this is fixed.

Sorry for all the trouble. Makefiles are fun! (not).

Yeah, maybe you had `CFG_DISABLE_DOC` (I think) set?

No problem! Your Makefile hacking saves the rest of us from it :-)
